{"_id":"8VUae7CIgCidvSfg","name":"Still Mind","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A monk of 3rd level or higher gains a +2 bonus on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Saving-Throws\">saving throws</a>&nbsp;against&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Enchantment\">enchantment</a>&nbsp;spells and effects.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Monk"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"ex","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/feats/blind-fight.jpg"}
{"name":"Relativity","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 15th level, you can traverse vertical surfaces as easily as you walk on the ground. When climbing, you move at your normal land speed and take none of the penalties associated with climbing. The surface must be able to support your weight, and difficult terrain affects your speed as normal. You are also immune to @Compendium[pf1.spells.3bdfw5f15hwcxlth]{Reverse Gravity}&nbsp;and similar effects.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"su","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/spells/leaf-orange-2.jpg","_id":"99nGhL2IYmQIiEZA"}
{"_id":"9EX00obqhGHcrOdp","name":"Fast Movement (BAR)","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A barbarian’s land speed is faster than the norm for her race by +10 feet. This benefit applies only when he is wearing no&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Armor-Bonus\">armor</a>, light&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Armor-Bonus\">armor</a>, or medium&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Armor-Bonus\">armor</a>, and not carrying a heavy load. Apply this bonus before modifying the barbarian’s speed because of any load carried or armor worn. This bonus stacks with any other bonuses to the barbarian’s land speed.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[{"formula":"10","operator":"+","target":"speed","subTarget":"landSpeed","modifier":"base","priority":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Barbarian"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"ex","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/armor_01.jpg"}
{"name":"Disorienting Touch","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 1st level, as a melee&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Touch-Attacks\">touch attack</a>, you can cause a creature to doubt its sense of depth and direction. The target is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Sickened\">sickened</a>&nbsp;for a number of rounds equal to 1/2 your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/sorcerer\">sorcerer</a>&nbsp;level (minimum 1). Multiple touches do not stack, but they do add to the duration. You can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 3 + your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Charisma</a>&nbsp;modifier.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"standard"},"duration":{"value":"mex(1, floor(@classes.sorcerer.level / 2))","units":"round"},"target":{"value":"creature touched"},"range":{"value":null,"units":"touch","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":3,"per":"day","autoDeductCharges":true,"maxFormula":"3 + @abilities.cha.mod"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"sp","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/ice_16.jpg","_id":"9Jr67vS43CgGUm5N"}
{"name":"Kobold Bloodline","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>The following bloodline is available to kobold sorcerers.</p>\n<p><em>While many kobold sorcerers tout their purely draconic bloodline, over generations of eldritch training, some such spellcasters have created a bloodline that, while tinged with some draconic magic, is the embodiment of the race’s virtue distilled into arcane form. Many practitioners of this bloodline go on to lead powerful kobold tribes.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Class Skill:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/disable-device\">Disable Device</a></p>\n<p><strong>Bonus Spells:</strong> @Compendium[pf1.spells.nee6cxpoekp3aklq]{Alarm}&nbsp;(3rd), @Compendium[pf1.spells.8w67l6dzzsi6oz5f]{Create Pit}&nbsp;(5th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.o4ywdvsm1oty8blq]{Explosive Runes}&nbsp;(7th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.cdedzw5d9ui73ua7]{Dragon's Breath}&nbsp;(9th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.bdyr9oebse6haser]{Transmute Rock to Mud}&nbsp;(11th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.8z4tlk1fojr9t9yb]{Guards and Wards}&nbsp;(13th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.cm3l4h4mld9j8lar]{Delayed Blast Fireball}&nbsp;(15th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.fv14vemq9gduhyhu]{Form Of The Alien Dragon III}&nbsp;(17th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.esia6azb5g68tfs7]{Imprisonment}&nbsp;(19th).</p>\n<p><strong>Bonus Feats:</strong> @Compendium[pf1.feats.Q1cY8r0Pvb66pMG0]{Alertness}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.u7rGDZUL296QIuA0]{Combat Casting}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.F9mKy0SmRo4bTdni]{Defensive Combat Training}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.JreaiTHdyWFNj3Tb]{Dodge}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.Uuiu3p982omhMEPj]{Improved Initiative}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.0bZf3SDkvVOe2ujH]{Lightning Reflexes}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.2YuxcUNFMPNBpekG]{Silent Spell}.</p>\n<p><a name=\"TOC-Bloodline-Arcana\"></a><strong>Bloodline Arcana:</strong> Whenever you cast a spell against a creature that is denied its&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Dexterity-Dex-\">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;bonus to AC, increase that spell’s DC by +2.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/races/kobold.png","_id":"9hNyAsFvgNzv0zGT"}
{"_id":"A3KJJHMNlAjUzcx6","name":"Change Shape","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 8th level, you can change your shape for a number of rounds per day equal to your wizard level. These rounds do not need to be consecutive. This ability otherwise functions like @Compendium[pf1.spells.774kmgcb7ygviht0]{Beast Shape II} or @Compendium[pf1.spells.pawbnw1nm4f0b98e]{Elemental Body I}. At 12th level, this ability functions like @Compendium[pf1.spells.w88ddxpu89qcr5c0]{Beast Shape III} or @Compendium[pf1.spells.yldjnorgbx4jsldz]{Elemental Body II}.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"standard"},"duration":{"value":"","units":"round"},"target":{"value":"Self"},"range":{"value":null,"units":"personal","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"day","autoDeductCharges":true,"maxFormula":"@classes.wizard.level"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Wizard"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"sp","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/blue_29.jpg"}
{"_id":"AL2Hf4j8cJozovGb","name":"Aquatic Bloodline","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Your family traces its heritage back to the ocean depths, whether scions of undersea empires left in the wake of nomadic sea-tribes, or the spawn of creeping ichthyic infiltrators into remote seaside villages. The song of the sea hums in your blood, calling the waves and all those within to your command.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Class Skill:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/swim\">Swim</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Bonus Spells:</strong> @Compendium[pf1.spells.ohy0ty2dawfaaqwd]{Hydraulic Push} (3rd), @Compendium[pf1.spells.7fvsn0gbv6ynlp63]{Slipstream}&nbsp;(5th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.a4z9yazsd7ez1p0h]{Aqueous Orb}&nbsp;(7th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.nll8ip8348eti0ff]{Geyser}&nbsp;(9th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.7yf67b7y4byj96w7]{Control Water}&nbsp;(11th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.br37848gchetel0q]{Beast Shape IV}&nbsp;(13th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.et3440o24hcgrfwl]{Summon Monster VII}&nbsp;(15th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.o4rwtizvdj7216qd]{Seamantle}&nbsp;(17th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.refg1teqkrdtxllg]{World Wave}&nbsp;(19th).</p>\n<p><strong>Bonus Feats:</strong>@Compendium[pf1.feats.rMR6ahXEfYqASE7D]{Athletic}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.nNVFVFRBCT4O2ab9]{Brew Potion}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.F9mKy0SmRo4bTdni]{Defensive Combat Training}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.JreaiTHdyWFNj3Tb]{Dodge}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.R7L4SlGRlnThqFrP]{Mobility}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.2YuxcUNFMPNBpekG]{Silent Spell}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.7zJTztNW7hdaqjKc]{Skill Focus}(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/swim\">Swim</a>), @Compendium[pf1.feats.8snLqsJN4LLL00Nq]{Toughness}.</p>\n<p><a name=\"TOC-Bloodline-Arcana\"></a><strong>Bloodline Arcana: </strong>Whenever you cast a spell of the water type, your effective&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Caster-Level\">caster level</a>&nbsp;is increased by one, and summoned creatures with a swim speed or the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Aquatic\">aquatic</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Water\">water</a>&nbsp;type gain a +1&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Morale-Bonus\">morale bonus</a>&nbsp;on attack and damage rolls.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/blue_20.jpg"}
{"_id":"ASjl9MkE7k5aYnaz","name":"Mage of the Veil Subschool","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Rather than controlling the elements or transforming the environment, mages of the veil focus on much more subtle magic—blending into their surroundings to watch, observe, and gather secrets, or fading from view completely for the sake of solitude. Most graduates of this college become spies, scouts, or infiltrators.</p>\n<p><strong>Associated School:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/wizard/arcane-schools/paizo-arcane-schools/classic-arcane-schools/illusion\">Illusion</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong> A mage of the veil must select&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/d/disguise-self\">disguise self</a>&nbsp;as one of his spells known at 1st level.</p>\n<p><strong>Class Skills:</strong> A mage of the veil gains&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/bluff\">Bluff</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/disguise\">Disguise</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/stealth\">Stealth</a>&nbsp;as class skills.</p>\n<p><strong>Replacement Powers:</strong> This subschool replaces the blinding ray and invisibility field powers of the <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Illusion\">illusion</a>&nbsp;school.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Wizard"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/spells/shielding-spirit-1.jpg"}
{"name":"Earth Crawler","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 15th level, you gain a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Burrow-Ex-\">burrow</a>&nbsp;speed of 30 feet. Additionally, as long as you are surrounded by at least 5 feet of dirt or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Natural-Armor-Bonus\">natural</a>&nbsp;stone on all sides, you gain&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules/#Fast_Healing_Ex\">fast healing</a>&nbsp;10. You can heal a number of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Hit-Points\">hit points</a>&nbsp;per day equal to 10 × your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/sorcerer\">sorcerer</a>&nbsp;level with this ability.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[{"formula":"30","priority":0,"target":"speed","subTarget":"burrowSpeed","modifier":"untyped"}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"su","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/yellow_42.jpg","_id":"AlrfaXXx2ywUvkqU"}
{"name":"Power of the Djinn","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 20th level, you gain the power of genies to grant wishes. Once per day, you can cast @Compendium[pf1.spells.s2p7a4biy7bl4ks2]{Limited Wish}&nbsp;as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Spell-Like-Abilities-Sp-\">spell-like ability</a>. Such wishes must begin with the words “I wish,” and cannot duplicate a @Compendium[pf1.spells.nnj51dwfkwd15ngj]{Wish}&nbsp;you have granted within the past 24 hours. If you use this ability to duplicate a spell with a costly material component, you must provide that component.</p>\n<p>You also become immune to electricity damage, and can use @Compendium[pf1.spells.q3st18udsalnyz5v]{Plane Shift}&nbsp;once per day to travel to or from the Plane of Air.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"su","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/spells/lightning-jade-3.jpg","_id":"AmWqjb41BCimEE2g"}
{"name":"Water's Fury","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 9th level, you gain the ability to summon a rushing jet of water from the elemental plane of water and direct it against your foes. As a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Standard-Actions\">standard action</a>, you can create a jet of water in a 60-foot line that deals 1d6 points of damage per two sorcerer levels you possess, and blinds the target that was struck for 1d6 rounds. A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Reflex\">Reflex</a>&nbsp;save (DC 10 + 1/2 your sorcerer level + your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Charisma</a>&nbsp;bonus) reduces the damage by half and negates the blinding effect.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"standard"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":"inst"},"target":{"value":"one creature"},"range":{"value":"60-ft. line","units":"spec","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"spellsave","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[["(floor(@classes.sorcerer.level / 2))d6","Cold"]],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":"","damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":"0","type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"sp","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/spells/needles-blue-1.jpg","_id":"Az0rp0Uf84Ee8PKJ"}
{"_id":"B1NZnF4kEwrmuUSu","name":"Blizzard","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 15th level, you can create a savage winter storm centered on you. This power acts as @Compendium[pf1.spells.g9koefk7x9szoheo]{Control Winds}, but in addition the entire area (not including the “eye” at the center of the storm) is affected as a @Compendium[pf1.spells.qnp4eosajai8s3sf]{Sleet Storm}&nbsp;and all in the area are exposed to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/environment/environmental-rules#TOC-Cold-Dangers\">extreme cold</a>. You may use this ability once per day.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"standard"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":1,"per":"day","autoDeductCharges":true,"maxFormula":"1"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"sp","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/ice_06.jpg"}
{"_id":"BO7BEFHDcf6qBaYV","name":"Combat Style Feat","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 2nd level, a ranger must select one&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/ranger/ranger-combat-styles/\">combat style</a>&nbsp;to pursue.</p>\n<p>The ranger’s expertise manifests in the form of bonus feats at 2nd, 6th, 10th, 14th, and 18th level. He can choose feats from his selected combat style, even if he does not have the normal prerequisites.</p>\n<p>The benefits of the ranger’s chosen style feats apply&nbsp;only&nbsp;when he wears light, medium, or no armor. He loses all benefits of his combat style feats when wearing heavy armor. Once a ranger selects a combat style, it cannot be changed.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Ranger"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"ex","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/feats/double-slice.jpg"}
{"_id":"BPRtCoYTMDwsITXJ","name":"Holy Champion","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 20th level, a paladin becomes a conduit for the power of her god. Her&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-damage-reduction\">DR</a> increases to 10/evil. Whenever she uses smite evil and successfully strikes an evil outsider, the outsider is also subject to a @Compendium[pf1.spells.trl849bibbe760xo]{Banishment}, using her paladin level as the caster level (her weapon and holy symbol automatically count as objects that the subject hates). After the @Compendium[pf1.spells.trl849bibbe760xo]{Banishment} effect and the damage from the attack is resolved, the smite immediately ends. In addition, whenever she channels positive energy or uses lay on hands to heal a creature, she heals the maximum possible amount.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Paladin"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"su","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/feats/spell-penetration.jpg"}
{"_id":"BS9WDbCy2Up3QHw9","name":"Scribe Scroll","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 1st level, a wizard gains @Compendium[pf1.feats.tlRu8SYjzA7WCHN7]{Scribe Scroll}&nbsp;as a bonus feat.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Wizard"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/items/inventory/note-scroll.jpg"}
{"_id":"BnbRdRnMftVioNiE","name":"Age Out","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 9th level, you gain the ability to instantly recover from most harmful effects by temporarily aging yourself decades in a matter of moments. As a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Standard-Actions\">standard action</a>, you can shift your effective age to the next highest aging step (for example, from adulthood to middle age). Each time you do this, any debilitating condition or effect currently affecting you that initially allowed a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Will\">Will</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Fortitude\">Fortitude</a>&nbsp;saving throw immediately ends. When you age yourself in this way, you take the normal penalties associated with growing older but gain none of the benefits. You cannot use this power to age beyond venerable, recover hit point damage, or remove effects that did not or do not allow a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Will\">Will</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Fortitude\">Fortitude</a>&nbsp;saving throw to negate. You return to your actual age 24 hours after the last time you used this ability, and all penalties to ability scores as a result of advanced age are then removed.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"standard"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"su","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/spells/rip-acid-1.jpg"}
{"_id":"BoEkMviJrW0PKmhj","name":"Trap Sense","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 3rd level, this character gains a +1 bonus on <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Reflex\" rel=\"nofollow\">Reflex</a>&nbsp;saves made to avoid traps and a +1&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#dodge_bonus\" rel=\"nofollow\">dodge bonus</a>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Armor-Class\" rel=\"nofollow\">armor class</a> against attacks made by traps. These bonuses increase by +1 every three levels thereafter (6th, 9th, 12th, 15th, and 18th level). Trap sense bonuses gained from multiple classes stack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Barbarian"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"ex","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/items/inventory/hook-hand.jpg"}
{"_id":"Bs5i98ja24ODe9WL","name":"Hunter's Bond","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 4th level, a ranger forms a bond with his hunting companions. This bond can take one of two forms. Once the form is chosen, it cannot be changed. The first is a bond to his companions. This bond allows him to spend a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Move-Actions\">move action</a>&nbsp;to grant half his&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/Ranger/#TOC-Favored-Enemy-Ex-\">favored enemy</a>&nbsp;bonus against a single target of the appropriate type to all allies within 30 feet who can see or hear him. This bonus lasts for a number of rounds equal to the ranger’s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wisdom</a>&nbsp;modifier (minimum 1). This bonus does not stack with any&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/Ranger/#TOC-Favored-Enemy-Ex-\">favored enemy</a>&nbsp;bonuses possessed by his allies; they use whichever bonus is higher.</p>\n<p>The second option is to form a close bond with an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions\">animal companion</a>. A ranger who selects an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions\">animal companion</a>&nbsp;can choose from the following list:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Badger\">badger</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Bird\">bird</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-camel\">camel</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Cat-Small\">cat (small)</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Rat-Dire\">dire rat</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Dog\">dog</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Horse\">horse</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Pony\">pony</a>, snake (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Snake-Viper\">viper</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Snake-Constrictor\">constrictor</a>), or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions#TOC-Wolf\">wolf</a>. If the campaign takes place wholly or partly in an aquatic environment, the ranger may choose a shark instead. This animal is a loyal companion that accompanies the ranger on his adventures as appropriate for its kind. A ranger’s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions\">animal companion</a>&nbsp;shares his&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/Ranger/#TOC-Favored-Enemy-Ex-\">favored enemy</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/Ranger/#TOC-Favored-Terrain-Ex-\">favored terrain</a>&nbsp;bonuses.</p>\n<p>This ability functions like the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid\">druid</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions\">animal companion</a>&nbsp;ability (which is part of the Nature Bond class feature), except that the ranger’s effective&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid\">druid</a>&nbsp;level is equal to his ranger level –3.</p>\n<p>A ranger can select a antelope, baboon, bustard, capybara, elk, falcon, kangaroo,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/animals/lizard/lizard-common\">lizard</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/animals/lizard/lizard-giant-gecko\">giant gecko</a>), marsupial devil, ram, reindeer,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/animals/snake\">snake</a>&nbsp;(reef snake or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/animals/snake/snake-cobra-spitting\">spitting cobra</a>), stag, trumpeter swan, thylacine, wolfdog, yak, or zebra as an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions\">animal companion</a>. If the campaign takes place in an aquatic environment, the ranger can choose an armorfish or reef snake. A falconer ranger can select a falcon companion instead of a bird companion.</p>\n<p>If the campaign takes place in an aquatic environment, the ranger can choose a stingray.</p>\n<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions/animal-companion-archetypes/ambusher-companion-archetype/\">ambusher</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions/animal-companion-archetypes/bully-companion-archetype/\">bully</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions/animal-companion-archetypes/daredevil-companion-archetype/\">daredevil</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions/animal-companion-archetypes/feytouched-companion-archetype/\">feytouched companion</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions/animal-companion-archetypes/precocious-companion-archetype/\">precocious companion</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions/animal-companion-archetypes/totem-guide-companion-archetype/\">totem guide</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions/animal-companion-archetypes/tracker-companion-archetype/\">tracker</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions/animal-companion-archetypes/verdant-companion-archetype/\">verdant companion</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions/animal-companion-archetypes/wrecker-companion-archetype/\">wrecker archetypes</a>&nbsp;are all particularly appropriate for a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/ranger\">ranger’s</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid/animal-companions\">animal companion</a>.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Ranger"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"ex","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/green_21.jpg"}
{"_id":"Bv4TWEti93H40Qbf","name":"Astral Bloodline","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Whether you were raised on the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/environment/the-planes#TOC-Astral-Plane\">Astral Plane</a>, had an ancestor with a strong connection to the Astral, or simply had a freak brush with an astral conduit in your youth, you have an unusual connection to both time and space. Your senses extend through the Astral Plane to the far reaches of the multiverse, allowing you to perceive and manipulate the timeless potential that binds the multiverse together. Your ancestors may have also held a connection to one of the astral isles or conduits, or like you, may have plied this cosmic ocean—and some may even survive there to this day.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Class Skill:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a>&nbsp;(planes).</p>\n<p><strong>Bonus Spells:</strong>@Compendium[pf1.spells.xco22162bwgxn7pj]{True Strike}&nbsp;(3rd), @Compendium[pf1.spells.3ze0kso9hxff5u2f]{False Life} (5th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.l7tmsbg37zr1q382]{Sands of Time}&nbsp;(7th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.ni93l43asrq29ytd]{Wandering Star Motes}&nbsp;(9th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.nsxngq65mbrzgwnm]{Permanency}&nbsp;(11th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.4br9puuneexco5hx]{Contingency}&nbsp;(13th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.btccs4sjo2nog1a0]{Ethereal Jaunt}&nbsp;(15th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.wniqskqkk0cubu9u]{Create Demiplane}&nbsp;(17th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.7mstq5c76h3e6zzx]{Time Stop} (19th).</p>\n<p><strong>Bonus Feats:</strong>@Compendium[pf1.feats.h9nHYLxXvIXBTmup]{Combat Reflexes}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.JreaiTHdyWFNj3Tb]{Dodge}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.HVu9JzllWoLzKKqH]{Forge Ring}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.Uuiu3p982omhMEPj]{Improved Initiative}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.0bZf3SDkvVOe2ujH]{Lightning Reflexes}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.wFoLrh5FeeqBXsQ8]{Quicken Spell}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.7zJTztNW7hdaqjKc]{Skill Focus}&nbsp;(<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a>&nbsp;[planes]), @Compendium[pf1.feats.vWiTqHC4Y3Xn1Pme]{Weapon Finesse}.</p>\n<p><strong>Bloodline Arcana: </strong>When you cast a spell, you can choose to enhance the next spell you cast before the end of your next turn, increasing the enhanced spell’s saving throw DC by 1. The level of the enhanced spell must be lower than that of the spell used to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Activate-Magic-Item\">activate</a>&nbsp;this ability.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/spells/haste-sky-3.jpg"}
{"_id":"ByK6tGzzELAxq67X","name":"Within Reach","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 15th level, your ultimate destiny is drawing near. Once per day, when an attack or spell that causes damage would result in your death, you may attempt a DC 20&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Saving-Throws\" rel=\"nofollow\">Will save</a>. If successful, you are instead reduced to –1 hit points and are automatically stabilized. The bonus from your fated ability applies to this save.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"su","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/gray_05.jpg"}
{"_id":"C5tWPm12qyz5ND9u","name":"Divine Health","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 3rd level, a paladin is immune to all diseases, including supernatural and magical diseases, including&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/afflictions/curses/mummy-rot\">mummy rot</a>.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Paladin"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"ex","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/feats/selective-channeling.jpg"}
{"_id":"CEjHiIRIDWGrJjMX","name":"Draconic Claws","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Starting at 1st level, you can grow claws as a free action. These claws are treated as natural weapons, allowing you to make two claw attacks as a full attack action using your full base attack bonus. Each of these attacks deals 1d4 points of damage plus your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a>&nbsp;modifier (1d3 if you are Small). At 5th level, these claws are considered magic weapons for the purpose of overcoming&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Damage-Reduction-DR-\">DR</a>. At 7th level, the damage increases by one step to 1d6 points of damage (1d4 if you are Small). At 11th level, these claws deal an additional 1d6 points of damage of your energy type on a successful hit. You can use your claws for a number of rounds per day equal to 3 + your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Charisma-Cha-\">Charisma</a>&nbsp;modifier. These rounds do not need to be consecutive.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"free"},"duration":{"value":"1","units":"round"},"target":{"value":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"units":"personal","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":3,"per":"day","autoDeductCharges":true,"maxFormula":"3 + @abilities.cha.mod"},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"su","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]},"identifiedName":"Draconic Claws"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/blood_06.jpg"}
{"_id":"CK5L0YJDENqBxLqv","name":"Fast Movement (MNK)","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 3rd level, a monk gains an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Enhancement-Bonus\">enhancement bonus</a>&nbsp;to his land speed, as shown on&nbsp;Table: monk. A monk in armor or carrying a medium or heavy load loses this extra speed.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[{"formula":"10*(floor(@classes.monk.level / 3))","operator":"+","target":"speed","subTarget":"landSpeed","modifier":"enh","priority":0}],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Monk"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"ex","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/feats/dodge.jpg"}
{"name":"Elemental Resistance (Fire)","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 3rd level, you gain&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-Energy-Resistance\">fire resistance</a>&nbsp;10. At 9th level, your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/special-abilities#TOC-Energy-Resistance\">fire resistance</a>&nbsp;increases to 20.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Sorcerer"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"ex","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/spells/protect-red-2.jpg","_id":"CSSEFVBegdWvHkDR"}
{"_id":"CV8BsY3ciUb9TA1Y","name":"Bonus Feats (FGT)","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 1st level, and at every even level thereafter, a fighter gains a bonus feat in addition to those gained from normal advancement (meaning that the fighter gains a feat at every level). These bonus feats must be selected from those listed as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/feats/combat-feats\">Combat Feats</a>, sometimes also called “fighter bonus feats.”</p>\n<p>Upon reaching 4th level, and every four levels thereafter (8th, 12th, and so on), a fighter can choose to learn a new bonus feat in place of a bonus feat he has already learned. In effect, the fighter loses the bonus feat in exchange for the new one. The old feat cannot be one that was used as a prerequisite for another feat, prestige class, or other ability. A fighter can only change one feat at any given level and must choose whether or not to swap the feat at the time he gains a new bonus feat for the level.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Fighter"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"none","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/affliction_18.jpg"}
{"_id":"Cc2eFfhJYlClCGEH","name":"Improved Evasion","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 9th level, a monk’s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/rogue#TOC-Evasion-Ex-\">evasion</a>&nbsp;ability improves. He still takes no damage on a successful&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Reflex\">Reflex</a>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Saving-Throws\">saving throw</a>&nbsp;against attacks, but henceforth he takes only half damage on a failed save. A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Helpless\">helpless</a>&nbsp;monk does not gain the benefit of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/rogue#TOC-Improved-Evasion-Ex-\">improved evasion</a>.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":"passive"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDeductCharges":true},"measureTemplate":{"type":"","size":0,"overrideColor":false,"customColor":"","overrideTexture":false,"customTexture":""},"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","critConfirmBonus":"","damage":{"parts":[],"critParts":[]},"attackParts":[],"formula":"","ability":{"attack":null,"damage":null,"damageMult":1,"critRange":20,"critMult":2},"save":{"dc":0,"type":"","description":""},"effectNotes":"","attackNotes":"","changes":[],"changeFlags":{"loseDexToAC":false,"noStr":false,"noDex":false,"oneInt":false,"oneWis":false,"oneCha":false,"noEncumbrance":false,"mediumArmorFullSpeed":false,"heavyArmorFullSpeed":false},"contextNotes":[],"links":{"children":[],"charges":[]},"featType":"classFeat","associations":{"classes":[["Monk"]]},"showInQuickbar":false,"abilityType":"ex","crOffset":"","attack":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/pf1/icons/skills/blue_06.jpg"}
{"name":"Efreeti Bloodline","permission":{"default":0,"kxj1AdlhCR0Bl1uR":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>You were born with the power of fire genies, and the magic of the efreet is strong in you.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Class Skill:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a>&nbsp;(planes).</p>\n<p><strong>Bonus Spells:</strong> @Compendium[pf1.spells.jnlr9cuepka1l26e]{Enlarge Person}&nbsp;(3rd), @Compendium[pf1.spells.q4ixxjb4v281g2xv]{Scorching Ray}&nbsp;(5th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.6oq1wcryviik9ice]{Fireball}&nbsp;(7th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.92hth51cs9oi0nfe]{Wall Of Fire}&nbsp;(9th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.enp0cwf0itsgjxv7]{Persistent Image}&nbsp;(11th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.qf4bqjgeff1q4hjt]{Planar Binding}&nbsp;(13th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.q3st18udsalnyz5v]{Plane Shift}&nbsp;(15th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.y4oyspjsp6cc7btp]{Giant Form II} (17th), @Compendium[pf1.spells.nnj51dwfkwd15ngj]{Wish}&nbsp;(19th).</p>\n<p><strong>Bonus Feats:</strong> @Compendium[pf1.feats.JreaiTHdyWFNj3Tb]{Dodge}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.77gXSucrxfrE9yWk]{Empower Spell}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.fVRnBIHR4Jq6btvm]{Great Fortitude}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.Uuiu3p982omhMEPj]{Improved Initiative}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.0bZf3SDkvVOe2ujH]{Lightning Reflexes}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.FUW5mIXHNBBIQ1Sq]{Power Attack}, @Compendium[pf1.feats.7zJTztNW7hdaqjKc]{Skill Focus} (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/knowledge\">Knowledge</a>&nbsp;[planes]), @Compendium[pf1.feats.vWiTqHC4Y3Xn1Pme]{Weapon Finesse}.</p>\n<p><strong>Bloodline Arcana:</strong> Whenever you cast a spell that deals energy damage, you can change the type of damage to fire. This also changes the spell’s descriptors to match this energy type.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"tags":[],"activation":{"cost":1,"type":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":""},"range":{"value":null,"units":"","long":null},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null,"autoDeduc